<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Note StyleSheet="xml/default_style.xml">    
    <Header MarginBottom="5%">
        <Title>#WISDOM - PRIDE</Title>
        <Speaker>Dr. Mark Moore</Speaker>
        <Date>September 27 &amp; 28, 2014</Date>
    </Header>

    <Quote MarginBottom="5%" Citation="Jon Foreman">
    	Greed, envy, sloth, pride and gluttony: these
    	are not vices anymore. No, these are marketing tools.
    </Quote>

    <Quote MarginBottom="5%" Citation="Proverbs 16:18">
    	Pride goes before destruction, a haughty spirit before a fall.
    </Quote>

    <Paragraph>Two kinds of pride:</Paragraph>
    <List>
    	<ListItem>
			<Paragraph>Pride that <RevealBox>BUILDS</RevealBox> up</Paragraph>
		</ListItem>
		
		<ListItem>
			<Paragraph>Pride that <RevealBox>PUFFS</RevealBox> up</Paragraph>
		</ListItem>
	</List>

	<Paragraph>Five tests for pride:</Paragraph>
    <List>
    	<ListItem>
			<Paragraph>If you <RevealBox>POINT FINGERS</RevealBox> when you are caught.</Paragraph>
		</ListItem>
		
		<ListItem>
			<Paragraph>If you <RevealBox>GET ANGRY</RevealBox> when you don&apos;t get what you &quot;deserve&quot;.</Paragraph>
		</ListItem>

		<ListItem>
			<Paragraph>If you don&apos;t <RevealBox>SEEK ADVICE</RevealBox> when you don&apos;t know your way.</Paragraph>
		</ListItem>

		<ListItem>
			<Paragraph>If you <RevealBox>AVOID CORRECTION</RevealBox> when you make a mistake.</Paragraph>
		</ListItem>

		<ListItem>
			<Paragraph>If you <RevealBox>TALK ABOUT YOURSELF</RevealBox> when you&apos;re with someone you respect.</Paragraph>
		</ListItem>
	</List>

	<Paragraph>Four antidotes for pride:</Paragraph>
    <List>
    	<ListItem>
			<Paragraph><RevealBox>SURROUND</RevealBox> yourself with honest people.</Paragraph>
		</ListItem>
		
		<ListItem>
			<Paragraph><RevealBox>SERVE</RevealBox> others who can&apos;t repay you.</Paragraph>
		</ListItem>

		<ListItem>
			<Paragraph><RevealBox>SURRENDER</RevealBox> your own:</Paragraph>
			<List>
				<ListItem><Paragraph>Position (Luke 14:7-11)</Paragraph></ListItem>
				<ListItem><Paragraph>Praise (Proverbs 27:2)</Paragraph></ListItem>
				<ListItem><Paragraph>Plans (James 4:13-17)</Paragraph></ListItem>
			</List>
		</ListItem>

		<ListItem>
			<Paragraph><RevealBox>SUFFER</RevealBox> under God&apos;s judgment.</Paragraph>
		</ListItem>
	</List>

	<Paragraph MarginTop="5%" >TAKE AWAY: What is the most important thing for you to do this week to <RevealBox>COMBAT PRIDE?</RevealBox></Paragraph>
</Note>
